author: Special to the Courier
title: Viking tennis nets third at league tournament
text: Viking tennis nets third at league tournament   Viking tennis team mixed their lineup around a bit for league play on Monday at McPherson. “We had some girls that wanted to play singles that haven’t had the chance and some that wanted to play doubles one last time,” coach Brian Shaw said. Mallory Meier played No. 1 singles and earned a third place medal after defeating Esau of Buhler 7-5, 7-6 (9). “Mallory got her money’s worth today, playing her last singles match of her high school career.
